Pre-emption
1. OS moves a thread from run to ready - a thread itself moves from runnning to blocked if it needs a resources or something to have run before
2. use of interrupts to pre-empt running thread
3. pre-emption - fairness to all threads - high prio runs before low prio -

CPU utilisation : % of available CPU cycles used
Wait time: time waited by a thread in ready queue
Turnaround time : time to complete each task - minimise this 

